 levels of solar activity. We show that the GPS method\nreturns accurate values of solar rotation independently of the level of solar\nactivity. In particular, it performs well during periods of high solar\nactivity, when TSI variability displays an irregular pattern and other methods\nfail. Our results suggest that the GPS method can successfully determine the\nrotational periods of stars with both regular and non-regular light-curves.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 9 Feb 2020 21:49:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-04-22"}
